parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the vehicle to shift out of gear, fail to accelerate, or jerk when shifting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks when shifting
fails to accelerate
shifts out of gear
the transmission icon illuminates on the instrument panel
the dashboard display shows scrambled letters or an "X" through the gear indicator
the vehicle is sluggish to drive
and the engine revs too high.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the neutral safety switch can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral or other gears while driving, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral or other gears while driving
the transmission icon illuminates on the instrument panel
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting
and the engine revs too high.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle positioning sensor can cause the engine to rev erratically, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine revs erratically
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may stall or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard stays on or flashes
the airbag warning light illuminates
the passenger airbag sensor misclassifies an adult as a child
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the seatbelt light comes on frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the airbag may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light stays on
the passenger airbag sensor misclassifies an adult as a child
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
the vehicle is destroyed or severely damaged
injuries or fatalities occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system can cause a fire, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the dashboard
headlights
or other electrical components; malfunctioning headlights
daytime running lights
or hazard lights; burning or melting of electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Jerking or hesitation when shifting gears
check engine light illumination
"HOLD" flashing on the dashboard
slow acceleration
and speedometer malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Lock and Airbag System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning door lock and airbag system can cause unintended door unlocking or locking, and airbag deployment issues, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unintended door unlocking or locking
airbag light illumination
and clicking or beeping sounds from the door locks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight and Daytime Running Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning headlights and daytime running lights can cause reduced visibility, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dim or malfunctioning headlights
daytime running lights staying on even when the car is turned off
and burning or melting of electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning tire pressure sensor can cause the tire pressure light to illuminate, potentially leading to tire failure or accidents.
symptoms: Tire pressure light illumination
and inconsistent or incorrect tire pressure readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Check Engine Light and Sensor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sensors and check engine light can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Check engine light illumination
stalling or hesitation
and malfunctioning sensors.
